That Time Larry Told me to Fuck Off

At one point in my life I was back in the same old town, the same old place—after having shot off like a rocket to New York City! And New York didn't fail me. It just got too commercial. The fun was gone. And I had to go somewhere and do something new. I went home; right back to Clemson [correct pronunciation], South Cackalacky. Home of the Sandlappers.

My parents had lived in that town for QUITE a while. What a paradise it was; what a child I was to not see it. But I had my chance to see it right.

